// The prior (Haiku) lead pass wrote a hallucinated `file:line` citation
// (12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md:607) into the one artefact the human reads directly.
// These pin the three markers the open-questions file cites, so they cannot silently rot.
{"id": "oq02-vnc-marker-line-pin", "kind": "file-line", "file": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "target": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "line": 364, "expect": "<!-- UNVERIFIED: `--vnc-experimental`", "claim": "OQ-02 cites the --vnc-experimental UNVERIFIED marker in 12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md. Pinned so the citation cannot rot. Re-derived by ledger at CROSS-AUDIT: the marker moved 340 -> 359 when harness expanded the file 535 -> 577 lines, and this claim FAILED LOUDLY rather than rotting silently. That failure is the mechanism working, not a defect. Formerly id oq02-vnc-marker-pinned-at-12-340. Paired with oq02-vnc-marker-exists-regardless-of-line (line-independent) and CONTROL-12-line-607-does-not-exist. Re-derived again at the human-decisions round: harness grew spec 12 to 607 lines and the marker moved 359 -> 364. The file-line claim FAILED LOUDLY rather than rotting; its line-independent companion oq02-vnc-marker-exists-regardless-of-line stayed green, which is how we know the marker MOVED rather than was DELETED. [final merge] Renamed from oq02-vnc-marker-line-pin: the marker has moved THREE times (340 -> 359 -> 364) and an id that names a line number rots even when the evidence is repaired. Line re-derived with grep -n at each move; currently 364. This claim is a TRIPWIRE that fires loudly on drift. The claim that actually PROTECTS the OQ-02 citation is the line-agnostic oq02-vnc-marker-exists-regardless-of-line: if BOTH fail the marker was DELETED; if only this one fails it merely MOVED."}
{"id": "CONTROL-12-line-607-does-not-exist", "kind": "file-line", "must_fail": true, "file": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "target": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "line": 607, "expect": "<!-- UNVERIFIED: `--vnc-experimental`", "claim": "CONTROL for oq02-vnc-marker-line-pin. THE ASSERTION IS: the --vnc-experimental marker is NOT at line 607 -- the exact citation the prior (Haiku) lead pass fabricated. It is NOT the assertion that 'line 607 does not exist'. The file is 577 lines today (was 535 when the control was written); an out-of-range line yields a plain False, which must_fail inverts, so growth alone never fires this. RESHAPED (lead ruling GB3): expect was the bare substring 'UNVERIFIED', which fired on ANY unrelated marker landing at line 607 -- proven against a synthetic 700-line file: ordinary prose at 607 PASSED, an UNRELATED marker at 607 raised a FALSE 'CONTROL PASSED - the oracle is broken'. A tripwire that cries wolf teaches its reader to disarm it. With the specific literal it fires only if the fabricated citation becomes genuinely valid, which is exactly the event worth screaming about. [GAP3] Its dependence on must_fail inverting a PLAIN failure is now proved by verifier-mustfail-inverts-a-plain-failure, which EXECUTES the tool against tests/fixtures/verifier/mustfail-inversion.jsonl \u2014 not by hand-testing recorded as prose.", "control": "verifier-mustfail-inverts-a-plain-failure", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "oq01-asif-marker-pinned-at-13-54", "kind": "file-line", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "target": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "line": 54, "expect": "<!-- UNVERIFIED: whether the same holds for `disk_format = \"asif\"`", "claim": "OQ-01 cites the disk_format=asif UNVERIFIED marker at 13-build-secrets.md:54. Pinned so the citation cannot rot. Re-verified by lead at SCAFFOLD; unlike OQ-02's, this citation was correct as written."}
