{"id": "g16-sensitive-masks-value-inside-unrelated-variable", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "env": {"PKR_VAR_pub": "ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL_AND_MORE"}, "expect": "<sensitive>_AND_MORE", "claim": "packer's sensitive=true redacts the VALUE wherever it appears, including inside a different, NON-sensitive variable: overriding var.pub to `ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL_AND_MORE` prints `<sensitive>_AND_MORE`. Masking is a substring rewrite over the output, not a property of the variable. This is why marking a common word (`admin`, G8's public default password) sensitive would rewrite every occurrence of that word in every log. POSITIVE CONTROL for g16-injected-secret-never-prints-in-unrelated-variable: same argv, same env, and it proves the command emits output at all."}
{"id": "g16-injected-secret-never-prints-in-unrelated-variable", "kind": "cli-help", "must_fail": true, "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "env": {"PKR_VAR_pub": "ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL_AND_MORE"}, "expect": "ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL_AND_MORE", "claim": "the sensitive value does not survive being smuggled into a non-sensitive variable: the injected literal never reaches packer's output. Alone this is unfalsifiable \u2014 an empty output satisfies it equally. Paired with g16-sensitive-masks-value-inside-unrelated-variable, which runs the SAME argv and SAME env and asserts `<sensitive>_AND_MORE` IS printed.", "control": "g16-sensitive-masks-value-inside-unrelated-variable", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "d1-justfile-build-golden-names-absent-template", "kind": "file-line", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "target": "Justfile", "line": 52, "expect": "packer build packer/tart-golden-image.pkr.hcl", "claim": "Justfile:52 names packer/tart-golden-image.pkr.hcl, which does not exist (paired with CONTROL-d1-packer-dir-does-not-exist, which proves the path is absent). [final merge] RETRACTED IN PART: this claim previously read '`just build-golden` is broken today' and pinned line 44. Both are now stale. The lead landed the OQ-04 guard: build-golden `test -f`s the template and exits 4 BEFORE reaching `packer build`, so the recipe now FAILS LOUDLY rather than being broken. Line re-derived 44 -> 52 with grep -n. The guard itself is pinned by justfile-build-golden-guards-on-missing-template and justfile-build-golden-guard-exits-4. `just build-golden` remains FORBIDDEN by scope, so the guard is evidenced by file-line, not by executing it."}
{"id": "CONTROL-d1-packer-dir-does-not-exist", "kind": "cli-help", "must_fail": true, "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["ls", "-1"], "expect": "packer", "claim": "there is no `packer/` directory at the repo root, so the template Justfile:44 invokes does not exist (D1). If this ever starts PASSING the template was authored \u2014 re-audit 13-build-secrets.md, which currently documents it as ABSENT. Alone this is unfalsifiable (no output satisfies it too); paired with CONTROL-ls-prints-repo-root-entries, which runs the SAME argv and asserts `Justfile` IS printed.", "control": "CONTROL-ls-prints-repo-root-entries", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "CONTROL-ls-prints-repo-root-entries", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["ls", "-1"], "expect": "Justfile", "claim": "POSITIVE CONTROL for CONTROL-d1-packer-dir-does-not-exist: `ls -1` from the repo root DOES print entries. If this fails, 'packer/ was absent from the listing' proves nothing \u2014 ls printed nothing."}
{"id": "d2-spec12-carries-the-phantom-recipe-retraction", "kind": "file-contains", "file": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "target": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "expect": "An earlier revision of this table documented `build [IMAGE]`", "claim": "D2 is FIXED: spec 12 no longer documents the phantom recipes as real; it carries an explicit retraction naming them. SUPERSEDES d2-spec12-201-documents-nonexistent-build-recipe, which pinned the defect at :201 and correctly began FAILING the moment harness repaired it. A claim that asserts a defect must be retired when the defect is, not silenced. No line number is pinned here, because the sentence \u2014 not its position \u2014 is the evidence."}
