{"id": "d5-justfile-63-discriminates-on-the-backtick", "kind": "file-line", "file": "specs/macos-ci/12-tooling-and-agent-loop.md", "target": "Justfile", "line": 71, "expect": "grep -v '`<!-- UNVERIFIED'", "claim": "D5' landed: unverified-count excludes backticked prose mentions, not the bare word. The brief's D5 claimed Justfile:63 grepped the bare word `UNVERIFIED` and that tightening to '<!-- UNVERIFIED' would drop 5 lines; both halves were false and the real discriminator is the backtick. Soundness of that discriminator is OQ-05."}

