{"id": "orchard-gold-tier-raises-limit-to-20-workers", "kind": "doc-contains", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "site": "tart", "page": "/orchard/quick-start/", "expect": "increase the limit to 20 Orchard Workers", "claim": "ORCHARD_LICENSE_TIER=gold raises the worker cap to 20. Independently corroborates 04's Gold row from a DIFFERENT page, which is what 04 \u00a72 claims to have cross-checked."}
{"id": "orchard-platinum-tier-raises-limit-to-200-workers", "kind": "doc-contains", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "site": "tart", "page": "/orchard/quick-start/", "expect": "increase the limit to 200 Orchard Workers", "claim": "ORCHARD_LICENSE_TIER=platinum raises the worker cap to 200. Corroborates 04's Platinum row from /orchard/quick-start/."}
{"id": "cirrus-cli-page-copies-working-directory", "kind": "doc-contains", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "site": "tart", "page": "/integrations/cirrus-cli/", "expect": "will copy over working directory", "claim": "The integrations page says cirrus run copies the working directory into the VM. It does NOT say HOW -- 'rsync' and '--dir' are both absent from the page, which is why 03:53 keeps its <!-- UNVERIFIED --> marker. Partially settled by cirrus-run-dirty-copies-unless-mounted."}
{"id": "cirrus-run-dirty-copies-unless-mounted", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "argv": ["cirrus", "run", "--help"], "expect": "the project directory files are copied, taking .gitignore into account", "claim": "cirrus run --help: by DEFAULT the project directory files are COPIED and .gitignore is honoured; --dirty MOUNTS the directory read-write instead. This settles copy-vs-mount and reveals a .gitignore filter that matters for a dotfiles harness. It does NOT name the transport (rsync vs tart --dir), so 03:53's marker survives, narrowed. This is a claim about what a flag DOES, so per the cli-help soundness rule it is paired with the doc evidence in cirrus-cli-page-copies-working-directory."}
{"id": "cirrus-worker-run-has-pool-registration-token", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "argv": ["cirrus", "worker", "run", "--help"], "expect": "pool registration token", "claim": "`cirrus worker run` takes a --token 'pool registration token' and a --name 'worker name to use when registering in the pool'. Persistent-worker registration therefore EXISTS in the shipped CLI. This REFUTES the stated reason of 03:144's marker ('no source page describes self-hosted Cirrus CI runner registration'): the CLI's own help describes it. Whether a persistent worker may run a CUSTOM tart image on hosted Cirrus CI remains unverified, so the marker stays with a corrected reason."}
