{"id": "no-terraform-provider-at-cirruslabs-tart", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "argv": ["curl", "-sS", "-o", "/dev/null", "-w", "%{http_code}", "https://registry.terraform.io/v1/providers/cirruslabs/tart"], "expect": "404", "claim": "G1: the Terraform Registry has no provider at the canonical address cirruslabs/tart. SCOPE OF THIS EVIDENCE: it refutes the canonical address ONLY. The registry's /v1/providers?q= search parameter is IGNORED (q=tart, q=utm and q=orchard all return the identical hashicorp/* top-100), so an EXHAUSTIVE negative over all namespaces is NOT established here and must not be claimed. Paired with no-terraform-provider-at-cirruslabs-orchard.", "control": "CONTROL-terraform-registry-serves-a-known-provider", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "no-terraform-provider-at-cirruslabs-orchard", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "argv": ["curl", "-sS", "-o", "/dev/null", "-w", "%{http_code}", "https://registry.terraform.io/v1/providers/cirruslabs/orchard"], "expect": "404", "claim": "G1: no Terraform provider at the canonical address cirruslabs/orchard either. Same scope caveat as no-terraform-provider-at-cirruslabs-tart: canonical address only, because the registry's q= search param is ignored.", "control": "CONTROL-terraform-registry-serves-a-known-provider", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "vanilla-tahoe-ssh-password-is-plain-admin-at-line-20", "kind": "file-line", "file": "specs/macos-ci/03-tart-ci-and-orchard.md", "target": "/Users/bossjones/dev/cirruslabs/macos-image-templates/templates/vanilla-tahoe.pkr.hcl", "line": 20, "expect": "ssh_password = \"admin\"", "claim": "Re-derived, not inherited: vanilla-tahoe.pkr.hcl:20 is ssh_password = \"admin\" (and :21 is ssh_username). 03:113 cites ':20-21' and the citation is CORRECT. These creds are PUBLIC and must never be marked sensitive (G16) -- doing so would redact the word 'admin' from every build log."}
