{"id": "synth-00-overview-grades-match-11-sources", "kind": "file-line", "target": "specs/macos-ci/00-overview.md", "line": 56, "expect": "graded meaty/thin/cited-as-exclusion", "file": "specs/macos-ci/00-overview.md", "claim": "CONFLICT L2, fixed and guarded. 00-overview.md advertised a '404' grade for 11-sources.md; 11-sources.md defines exactly three grades and states outright that no [404] grade exists because nothing is dead. A direct contradiction between two files the same agent owns. The '404' grade was G10 residue: it existed only because the brief believed four URLs were dead. Pinned so the retracted grade cannot reappear."}
{"id": "synth-07-appendix-declares-no-dead-links", "kind": "file-contains", "target": "specs/macos-ci/07-utm-settings-appendix.md", "expect": "## Dead links \u2014 none", "file": "specs/macos-ci/00-overview.md", "claim": "CONFLICT L1, fixed and guarded. 00-overview.md:52 restated RETRACTED G10 as fact ('4 pruned dead URLs'). There are none: 07-utm-settings-appendix.md is literally headed '## Dead links -- none', and 11-sources.md carries the full G10 retraction. Every downstream file had been fixed; the orientation file had not. This claim ties 00's new sentence to 07's actual heading, so if 07 ever regains a dead-links section the overview's denial fails loudly instead of drifting."}
{"id": "synth-packer-version-is-1-15-4", "kind": "cli-help", "argv": ["packer", "version"], "expect": "Packer v1.15.4", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "G14, RETRACTED. The master brief asserted packer was NOT installed. It is, at v1.15.4. 11-sources.md:143 already asserted 'v1.15.4' in prose with no ledger entry behind it; this closes that gap. Stronger than packer-is-installed (expect 'Packer v1.'), which would survive any 1.x. If this fails, the host packer changed and every packer cli-help claim must be re-captured, not trusted -- same role tart-version-is-2-32-1 plays for the 92 tart/utmctl probes."}
{"id": "synth-justfile-has-no-doctor-recipe", "kind": "absent", "target": "Justfile", "expect": "doctor:", "control": "justfile-check-is-the-gate", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "G14, second half, RETRACTED. The brief pointed agents at a `just doctor` recipe to install packer. No such recipe exists: `just --summary` lists build-golden check default link-check link-check-fresh link-check-verbose unverified-count verify-claims verify-claims-json verify-no-secrets. Negative evidence, so it names a positive control on the SAME file -- an absent claim passes against a gutted or deleted Justfile, which is the GB4 hazard this very retraction documents.", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "synth-openai-tart-license-is-fsl-1-1", "kind": "http-contains", "url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openai/tart/main/LICENSE", "expect": "Functional Source License, Version 1.1", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "OQ-20. tart's LICENSE at its new canonical home (openai/tart) is FSL-1.1-ALv2, copyright 2022-2026 OpenAI. Positive control for synth-fsl-text-never-mentions-cores: proves the probe CAN see this URL's body, so 'no cores' cannot pass because the fetch returned nothing."}
{"id": "synth-fsl-text-never-mentions-cores", "kind": "http-contains", "url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openai/tart/main/LICENSE", "expect": "core", "must_fail": true, "polarity": "negative", "control": "synth-openai-tart-license-is-fsl-1-1", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "OQ-20. The FSL licence TEXT mentions cores ZERO times. The 100-core Free Tier is therefore a GRANT PUBLISHED ON tart.run, not a clause of the licence. Both can be true at once, and conflating them would mean reading a core limit into a document that has none. Negative evidence: controlled by synth-openai-tart-license-is-fsl-1-1 on the same URL."}
{"id": "synth-tart-licensing-page-never-mentions-openai", "kind": "doc-contains", "site": "tart", "page": "/licensing/", "expect": "OpenAI", "must_fail": true, "polarity": "negative", "control": "tart-licensing-contact-is-cirruslabs", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "OQ-20, contact half DOUBTFUL. tart.run/licensing mentions OpenAI zero times: it still says Fair Source, still grants the 100-core Free Tier, still lists licensing@cirruslabs.org -- three months after the acquisition announcement. The page is STALE RELATIVE TO THE ACQUISITION. This claim is why 04 must NOT assert who enforces; it marks that UNVERIFIED citing OQ-20."}
{"id": "synth-grep-over-cirruslabs-clones-emits-real-paths", "kind": "cli-help", "argv": ["grep", "-rIl", "DiskFormat", "/Users/bossjones/dev/cirruslabs/"], "expect": "/packer-plugin-tart/", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "Positive control for synth-packer-plugin-clone-free-of-fixture-sentinel. Same command SHAPE over the same substrate with a pattern known to match. The literal '/packer-plugin-tart/' is one no grep ERROR path can produce, per the GB1 lesson: a control keyed on a literal an error message also contains ('fatal:', ':') proves nothing. If the clones vanish, this control fails loudly instead of letting the negative pass."}
{"id": "synth-packer-plugin-clone-free-of-fixture-sentinel", "kind": "cli-help", "argv": ["grep", "-rIl", "ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL", "/Users/bossjones/dev/cirruslabs/"], "expect": "/packer-plugin-tart/", "must_fail": true, "polarity": "negative", "control": "synth-grep-over-cirruslabs-clones-emits-real-paths", "file": "specs/macos-ci/11-sources.md", "claim": "OQ-32. The reference clones are FREE of the fixture sentinel this run's own pre_tool_use hook wrote into them. A grep -rIl negative emits ZERO BYTES on a true negative, so no same-argv control is possible (the GB2 shape); the control runs the same shape over the same substrate with a pattern that does match. This is what makes 02:172-177 upheld with NO --exclude-dir=logs: the contamination is gone at the SOURCE, and the spec never had to accommodate a defect in our own tooling."}
{"id": "CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-emits-info-banner", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "packer inspect tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive 2>&1 1>/dev/null"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "1"}, "expect": "[INFO] Packer version:", "claim": "DISCRIMINATOR + positive control. Isolates STDERR (2>&1 1>/dev/null) so stdout cannot satisfy it. Proves PACKER_LOG=1 really produced a debug log: 845B on stderr vs 0B without. Partner of packer-sensitive-hides-secret-in-isolated-debug-log."}
{"id": "CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-prints-plain-literal", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "packer inspect tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive 2>&1 1>/dev/null"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "1"}, "expect": "plain_FIXTURE_CONTROL", "claim": "POSITIVE CONTROL, same argv+env as packer-sensitive-hides-secret-in-isolated-debug-log: the debug log on stderr DOES carry non-sensitive literals, so 'the secret is absent from stderr' is not satisfied by an empty stderr. REFINES 13:297, which says plain_FIXTURE_CONTROL 'appears on stdout' -- it appears on BOTH streams under the overlay."}
{"id": "packer-sensitive-hides-secret-in-isolated-debug-log", "kind": "cli-help", "must_fail": true, "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "packer inspect tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive 2>&1 1>/dev/null"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "1"}, "expect": "ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL", "claim": "The sensitive value is absent from the DEBUG LOG ITSELF, not merely from a stdout+stderr blob that stdout could have satisfied alone. This is the properly-powered successor to packer-sensitive-hides-secret-under-debug-log, whose control (CONTROL-packer-debug-log-prints-plain-literals) matches a literal that stdout prints identically with and without the overlay. Paired with CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-emits-info-banner (log exists) and CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-prints-plain-literal (stream non-empty).", "polarity": "negative", "control": "CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-prints-plain-literal"}
{"id": "packer-no-debug-log-on-stderr-when-overlay-disabled", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "test -z \"$(packer inspect tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive 2>&1 1>/dev/null)\" && echo NO_DEBUG_LOG_ON_STDERR"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "0"}, "expect": "NO_DEBUG_LOG_ON_STDERR", "claim": "PACKER_LOG=0 => stderr is EMPTY (0 bytes), so the overlay is what CAUSES the debug log. Written as a POSITIVE assertion (echoes a token) rather than a bare must_fail, because 'no [INFO] line' is also satisfied by no output at all. env pins '0' rather than omitting the key: cli-help merges env over os.environ and cannot UNSET (OQ-14).", "control": "CONTROL-packer-debug-log-stderr-emits-info-banner", "polarity": "negative"}
{"id": "packer-log-value-off-still-enables-logging", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "packer inspect tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive 2>&1 1>/dev/null"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "off"}, "expect": "[INFO] Packer version:", "claim": "Backs 13:316. PACKER_LOG is NOT parsed as a boolean: the literal string 'off' ENABLES debug logging. Only unset, '' and '0' disable it; 'off', 'false', 'no', '00' and ' ' all enable. An operator who 'turned logging off' with PACKER_LOG=off has turned it ON."}
{"id": "packer-shell-use-env-var-file-has-no-default-assignment", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "f=$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hashicorp/packer/v1.15.4/provisioner/shell/provisioner.go); printf '%s' \"$f\" | grep -q 'UseEnvVarFile bool' || { echo FETCH_FAILED; exit 0; }; printf '%s' \"$f\" | grep -qE 'UseEnvVarFile[[:space:]]*=[^=]' && echo HAS_DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENT || echo NO_DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENT"], "expect": "NO_DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENT", "claim": "SETTLES ledger's OQ-09. packer v1.15.4 provisioner/shell/provisioner.go declares `UseEnvVarFile bool` (:46) and NEVER assigns it -- it is only READ via `== true` (:103, :110, :241). So `use_env_var_file` defaults to Go's zero value, false. The DOCS page never states this default (it states one for skip_clean and not for use_env_var_file), so 13:174's `# default` was an inference until now. Guarded against a silent network failure: the probe first requires `UseEnvVarFile bool` to be present and echoes FETCH_FAILED otherwise, so an empty download CANNOT satisfy the expect."}
{"id": "packer-shell-varfile-is-chmod-0600-in-guest", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["sh", "-c", "f=$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hashicorp/packer/v1.15.4/provisioner/shell/provisioner.go); printf '%s' \"$f\" | grep -q 'UseEnvVarFile bool' || { echo FETCH_FAILED; exit 0; }; printf '%s' \"$f\" | grep -o 'chmod 0600 %s' | head -1"], "expect": "chmod 0600 %s", "claim": "Backs 13:90. The uploaded env-var file is chmod 0600 on the guest (provisioner.go:279). 0600 protects it from other guest users; it does NOT protect it from `strings` on the host's disk image, which is the whole point of 13. Same FETCH_FAILED guard as packer-shell-use-env-var-file-has-no-default-assignment."}
