{"id": "tart-licensing-page-never-mentions-openai", "kind": "http-contains", "must_fail": true, "polarity": "negative", "control": "tart-licensing-page-still-says-free-tier", "file": "specs/macos-ci/04-tart-licensing-risk.md", "url": "https://tart.run/licensing/", "expect": "OpenAI", "claim": "NEGATIVE (polarity per OQ-37). tart.run/licensing/ contains the string 'OpenAI' ZERO times, though the code's copyright holder is now OpenAI. The tier-grant page is STALE relative to the April 2026 acquisition. Its evidence must NOT verify. Unfalsifiable alone \u2014 an empty page, a 404, or a network outage would all satisfy 'OpenAI is absent' \u2014 so it is PAIRED with tart-licensing-page-still-says-free-tier, which greps the SAME URL for a literal that IS present. If this ever starts passing, tart.run was updated and 04 \u00a74b's UNVERIFIED marker can be retired."}
